data.description: Move-in ready home in the fabulous River Walk neighborhood, home of the River Walk Shockwaves!  Wonderful neighborhood amenities include 4 mile, paved and tree lined walking path along the flowing river.  Prime Location in the heart of Five Forks. This 5 bed/3.5 bath + den, brick home sits quietly nestled at the heart of this cul de sac and boasts a spacious two car garage with additional private parking large enough for 6 additional cars.  Primary suite located on the main floor, butler’s pantry, den, and large separate garage storage. The front and rear grounds have been well maintained, and the backyard offers a peaceful, private park like setting. As you enter the foyer, the family room/den is to your right, and greets the formal dining room. Through the butler’s pantry you enter into the kitchen and breakfast nook.   There is a half bathroom off the foyer as well. The living room boasts a gas log fireplace and opens to the kitchen from the other side of the home. The large kitchen includes double ovens, instant hot water at the sink and stainless steel appliances.  This kitchen has so many cabinets and drawers you can store all of your cooking and kitchen related gadgets!  The laundry is off of the kitchen and just outside of the primary bedroom for easy access.   Upstairs there are 4 bedrooms.   All these rooms are spacious and have large, walk-in closets.  Two of the rooms share a jack and jill bathroom and another full bath is accessible through the hallway.   Crawl space has been recently renovated to include new sump pumps, dehumidifier and moisture barrier.  River Walk neighborhood includes an excellent amenity package including Jr. Olympic size swimming pool, tennis courts, recreational room, workout facility and of course, the river.  This home is located close to shopping, dining, interstate access and medical facilities.  7 Black Pine Court is waiting for you!  Listing agent is related to seller.
